comment.author: 26881258@N07
comment._content: A very crowded German seaplane station in WW1, but no Rumpler 6B1 single seat fighter seaplanes. I could see. In the front a Friedrichshafen FF 33h (Marinenummer '732') and a Friedrichshafen FF 33e (Marinummer '899'). Both two-seater seaplanes. '732' is hoisted by a crane to get in the water or maybe it is just hoisted out of the water.
